#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L03_RintroRcases
msgid "# Pattern-Matching Introduction: rintro and rcases\n"
"\n"
"In Level 2, the proof of the image property took four steps:\n"
"§0, §1, §2, then work.\n"
"\n"
"Lean offers a power tool that collapses this: **§3**. It combines\n"
"§4 with deep pattern matching in a single step. The key feature\n"
"is the **§5 pattern**: when you write §6 inside the pattern,\n"
"it automatically substitutes the equation instead of naming it.\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"For image membership §8 (which is §9),\n"
"this gives you:\n"
"- §10 -- the witness\n"
"- §11 -- the membership proof\n"
"- The equation §12 is consumed by §13, which replaces §14\n"
"  with §15 everywhere\n"
"\n"
"Compare the two approaches:\n"
"\n"
"| Steps | Old way | With rintro |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| 1 | §16 | §17 |\n"
"| 2 | §18 | (done!) |\n"
"| 3 | §19 | |\n"
"\n"
"The **§20** tactic does the same pattern matching on an existing\n"
"hypothesis: §21.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that if §22 is in the image of the \"triple\"\n"
"function on numbers less than 4, then §23. Use §24 for\n"
"a two-step proof."
msgstr ""

