#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L13_SetNonEquality
msgid "# When Two Sets Are Not Equal\n"
"\n"
"In Levels 10–12, you proved set equalities using §0. But what if\n"
"two sets are NOT equal? How do you prove §1?\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §2 is defined as §3. So to prove\n"
"§4, you use §5 to **assume** the sets are equal, getting\n"
"§6, and then derive a contradiction (§7).\n"
"\n"
"The strategy mirrors Level 7 (disproving §8): **find a witness** that\n"
"leads to contradiction. If §9, then every element of §10 is in §11\n"
"and vice versa. Find an element that is in one set but not the other —\n"
"then the assumption §12 forces a false arithmetic conclusion.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, you will prove §13. The\n"
"witness is §14: it satisfies §15 (so §16 is in the right set) but\n"
"not §17 (so §18 is not in the left set). If the sets were equal,\n"
"§19 would have to be in both — contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §20 — assume the sets are equal\n"
"2. Prove §21 — show the witness is in the right set\n"
"3. Use §22 to transport: if equal, §23\n"
"4. Unwrap and derive contradiction — §24 is false"
msgstr ""

