#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L07_BoundedIUnion
msgid "# Bounded Indexed Unions\n"
"\n"
"So far, the indexed union §0 ranges over ALL values of the\n"
"index type §1. But often you want to restrict the index to a subset.\n"
"For example, if you have sets indexed by all natural numbers but only\n"
"care about the first ten, §2 restricts the\n"
"union to those ten indices. Bounded variants let you union or intersect\n"
"over a sub-collection without changing the index type.\n"
"\n"
"More precisely:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this is written §4.\n"
"\n"
"**New tool**: §5 converts membership in a bounded\n"
"indexed union into a **double existential**:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"The key difference from unbounded §7 is that after providing\n"
"the witness index §8, you must ALSO prove that §9. This gives\n"
"a two-step §10 pattern:\n"
"\n"
"1. §11 — provide the witness index\n"
"2. §12 — provide the proof that §13\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that §14 when §15. This\n"
"is the bounded analogue of Level 4 (§16), with the\n"
"extra obligation of proving the index is in bounds."
msgstr ""

