#: Game.Levels.InjectiveWorld.L04_Composition
msgid "# Composing Injective Functions\n"
"\n"
"If §0 and §1 are both injective, then their composition §2 is\n"
"also injective. Intuitively: if neither §3 nor §4 collapses distinct\n"
"inputs, then doing §5 followed by §6 cannot collapse them either.\n"
"\n"
"The proof uses the canonical shape, then applies both injectivity\n"
"hypotheses in sequence:\n"
"\n"
"1. Assume §7, i.e., §8\n"
"2. Since §9 is injective: §10\n"
"3. Since §11 is injective: §12\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §13 reduces the goal from §14 to §15\n"
"(because §16 says §17). Similarly\n"
"for §18.\n"
"\n"
"**New proof move**: chain §19 through two injectivity hypotheses."
msgstr ""

