#: Game.Levels.PreimageWorld.L11_PreimageIndexedUnion
msgid "# Existentials Pass Through Too\n"
"\n"
"You proved that preimage preserves binary union:\n"
"§0. The logical reason was that\n"
"§1 passes through function application.\n"
"\n"
"Indexed union generalizes binary union from §2 to §3:\n"
"§4 means §5. Does preimage preserve\n"
"this too?\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"Yes — for the same reason. The left side says §7,\n"
"and the right side says §8, which is also\n"
"§9. The existential quantifier passes through\n"
"function application unchanged.\n"
"\n"
"**A change in proof technique**: Unlike binary intersection and\n"
"union (which unfold definitionally), indexed union membership\n"
"§10 requires an explicit rewrite with\n"
"§11. This is because indexed union (§12) is defined\n"
"differently from binary union (§13) in Lean — the indexed version\n"
"uses a more general construction that does not reduce by\n"
"definitional unfolding.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §14 then §15\n"
"2. **Forward**: The hypothesis is a preimage membership. Use\n"
"   §16 to unwrap it, then §17\n"
"   to expose the §18. Destructure and reassemble.\n"
"3. **Backward**: The hypothesis is an indexed union. Use\n"
"   §19 directly, destructure, then reassemble\n"
"   with §20 and §21."
msgstr ""

