msgid "You proved §0.\n"
"\n"
"The proof used ONE witness §1 from §2, which belongs to\n"
"ALL §3 simultaneously. For each index §4, the same §5 serves as\n"
"witness for §6.\n"
"\n"
"**Why equality fails**: The reverse direction would require: given\n"
"separate witnesses §7 for each §8 (all with §9),\n"
"finding a single §10 with §11. If §12 is not\n"
"injective, the witnesses §13 might all be different, and no single\n"
"§14 might be in every §15.\n"
"\n"
"**Concrete counterexample**: Let §16, with §17\n"
"and §18 (indexed by §19). Then §20\n"
"(no element is in both), so §21. But\n"
"§22 and §23, so\n"
