#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L02_IndexedIntersection
msgid "# Indexed Intersections\n"
"\n"
"Just as §0 generalizes §1, the **indexed intersection** §2\n"
"generalizes §3:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"An element is in the indexed intersection if it belongs to **every**\n"
"set in the family. The binary intersection §5 is the special\n"
"case with a two-element index:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Notation | Logical meaning |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| Binary intersection | §6 | §7 |\n"
"| Indexed intersection | §8 | §9 |\n"
"\n"
"**New tool**: §10 converts §11 into\n"
"§12. After that, you introduce the universally quantified\n"
"variable with §13.\n"
"\n"
"**About §14**: The index type here is §15, which represents\n"
"the natural numbers less than 4: §16. After §17,\n"
"you get §18. Use §19 to access its numerical value.\n"
"This bounded type ensures the intersection is over finitely many sets.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: The family §20 for §21\n"
"gives four sets: {n | 0 ≤ n}, {n | 1 ≤ n}, {n | 2 ≤ n}, {n | 3 ≤ n}.\n"
"Prove that §22 belongs to all of them."
msgstr ""

