"\n"
"If §0, then §1. In words: if a target set\n"
"grows, the preimage grows too.\n"
"\n"
"Why? If §2 maps into §3 (a subset of §4), then §5 certainly maps\n"
"into §6.\n"
"\n"
"This is your first abstract preimage proof — the function §7 is\n"
"no longer a specific function like §8, but an arbitrary\n"
"function.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §9 — start the subset proof\n"
"2. Now §10, which is definitionally §11\n"
"3. The subset hypothesis §12 is a function: given §13,\n"
"   it produces §14\n"
"4. Apply §15 to §16 to get §17, which is §18"
msgstr ""

