#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L19_DeMorganInter
msgid "# De Morgan's Law for Indexed Intersections\n"
"\n"
"In the previous level, you proved that §0, which is the set version of\n"
"§1.\n"
"\n"
"Now prove the **dual**: §2,\n"
"which is the set version of §3.\n"
"\n"
"**Why this is harder**: The previous direction (§4) is constructive — if no witness exists, you can show the\n"
"property holds for all indices directly. But the current direction\n"
"(§5) is **classical**: knowing that\n"
"\"not all sets contain x\" does not directly hand you a specific set\n"
"that excludes x. You need proof by contradiction (§6) to find\n"
"the witness.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan for the forward direction** (§7):\n"
"1. Assume the goal is false (§8)\n"
"2. Show that this forces §9 — contradicting the hypothesis\n"
"3. To show §10 for arbitrary §11, assume §12 and derive\n"
"   a contradiction with the by_contra hypothesis\n"
"\n"
"The backward direction is constructive and follows the same pattern as\n"
"the previous level."
