#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld
msgid "# Image World\n"
"\n"
"You have mastered preimages -- pulling sets back through functions. Now you\n"
"will study the dual operation: **images** -- pushing sets forward.\n"
"\n"
"Given a function §0 and a set §1 (a set of inputs),\n"
"the **image** of §2 under §3 is the set of all outputs that come from\n"
"inputs in §4:\n"
"\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this is written §6 (type §7).\n"
"\n"
"**The critical difference from preimage**: Image membership involves an\n"
"**existential**. To prove §8, you must **exhibit a witness** --\n"
"an input §9 such that §10. Preimage membership was just\n"
"function application (§11 -- no witness needed).\n"
"Image membership requires a construction.\n"
"\n"
"This existential has far-reaching consequences:\n"
"- Image preserves union: **yes** (equality)\n"
"- Image preserves intersection: **no** (only ⊆, not =)\n"
"- Image preserves complement: **no**\n"
"\n"
"Compare with preimage, which preserves ALL set operations. The\n"
"difference comes down to logic: preimage uses §12, §13, §14 which\n"
"commute with function application. Image uses §15, which does NOT\n"
"commute with §16 or §17.\n"
"\n"
"By the end of this world, you will:\n"
"- Prove image membership by exhibiting witnesses\n"
"- Learn §18 and §19 -- power tools for pattern matching\n"
"- Prove §20 -- the vacuous extremal case\n"
"- Prove §21 -- the simplest image\n"
"- Prove image preserves union but NOT intersection\n"
"- See a concrete counterexample for intersection equality\n"
"- Prove image distributes over function composition\n"
"- Learn §22 -- the image of everything\n"
"- Prove that §23\n"
"- Prove the Galois connection: §24\n"
"- Explore the image-preimage gaps and when they close\n"
"- Re-derive monotonicity AND the image-preimage gap from the Galois connection\n"
"- Prove image preserves nonemptiness (both directions)\n"
"\n"
"The boss asks you to prove that §25 when every element\n"
"of §26 is in the range of §27 -- the image-preimage gap closes with a\n"
"surjectivity condition.\n"
"\n"
"**New notation**: §28 (typed §29) -- the image of §30 under §31.\n"
"\n"
"**New tactics**: §32 and §33 -- pattern-matching introduction\n"
"and case analysis. You will also use §34 (from Set World) extensively\n"
"with a new pattern: §35.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: Set World, Subset World, Set Operations World,\n"
"Preimage World."
msgstr ""

