#: Game.Levels.PsetSets.L16_AbsorptionLaw
msgid "You proved the absorption law §0.\n"
"\n"
"The proof was simple but illustrates an important point: the forward\n"
"direction required only that §1 (which is always true), and\n"
"the backward direction required only that §2 (also\n"
"always true). Absorption holds because intersection makes things\n"
"*smaller* (so §3 adds nothing to §4).\n"
"\n"
"**The dual absorption law** §5 also holds: intersecting\n"
"§6 with §7 keeps exactly the elements of §8, because every\n"
"element of §9 is automatically in §10. The proof uses the same\n"
"structure with swapped roles of §11 and §12.\n"
"\n"
"**Boolean algebra scorecard** — Phase 1 has now covered:\n"
"- Commutativity: §13, §14\n"
"- Distributivity: §15\n"
"- De Morgan: §16, §17\n"
"- Complement laws: §18, §19\n"
"- Double complement: §20\n"
"- Absorption: §21"
msgstr ""

