#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L02_ChangeTactic
msgid "# Unwrapping Hypotheses with §0\n"
"\n"
"In Level 1, you used §1 to unwrap the **goal** from set notation\n"
"to arithmetic, and §2 to extract the hypothesis content. Both\n"
"techniques work, but there is a more direct tool for hypotheses.\n"
"\n"
"The tactic §3 converts §4 to display as §5, just\n"
"as §6 does for the goal. Both require §7 to be\n"
"**definitionally equal** to the current type. They only change the\n"
"*display*, not the *meaning*.\n"
"\n"
"After §8, the hypothesis §9 is\n"
"definitionally §10. Use §11 to make this\n"
"explicit. Then §12 unwraps the goal, and §13\n"
"closes it — since being strictly less than 3 implies being at most 3.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §14 — fix an element and assume §15\n"
"2. §16 — unwrap the hypothesis to arithmetic\n"
"3. §17 — unwrap the goal to arithmetic\n"
"4. §18 — derive §19 from §20"
