#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L14_DualDeMorgan
msgid "# Dual De Morgan: (s ∩ t)ᶜ = sᶜ ∪ tᶜ\n"
"\n"
"In Level 12, you proved §0. Now prove the\n"
"**dual**: the complement of an intersection is the union of the\n"
"complements:\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"The proof has a **genuinely different structure** from the union version.\n"
"The forward direction requires a new technique: **proof by contradiction**.\n"
"\n"
"**New tactic: §2**\n"
"\n"
"When you cannot build the goal directly, assume its negation and derive\n"
"a contradiction:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"**Why is this needed here?** The forward direction gives you\n"
"§4 and asks for §5. You cannot\n"
"directly choose §6 or §7 without knowing which of §8 or\n"
"§9 fails. But if you assume the goal is FALSE (§10),\n"
"then §11 converts §12 to §13\n"
"— which contradicts §14.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §15, §16\n"
"2. **Forward**: §17, §18, §19 + §20, §21\n"
"3. **Backward**: §22, §23, destructure and case-split"
msgstr ""

