#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L09_ComplementLaw
msgid "# s ∩ sᶜ = ∅\n"
"\n"
"The most fundamental fact about complements is that a set and its\n"
"complement have **no elements in common**:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"This makes sense: §1 means §2 AND §3, which is\n"
"a contradiction. So no element can belong to both.\n"
"\n"
"**Proving a set equals ∅**: Use §4 to reduce to\n"
"§5. Since §6 is definitionally §7,\n"
"the forward direction asks you to derive a contradiction from\n"
"§8, and the backward direction asks you to prove anything\n"
"from §9.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §10 then §11\n"
"2. **Forward**: §12, then §13 to get\n"
"   §14 and §15. Apply §16 to §17.\n"
"3. **Backward**: §18 — but §19, so use §20."
msgstr ""

