#: Game.Levels.PsetSets.L18_Boss
msgid "# Boss: De Morgan's Law for Indexed Unions\n"
"\n"
"Prove the indexed De Morgan law:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"In words: an element is outside the union of a family if and only if\n"
"it is outside every member of the family.\n"
"\n"
"You proved this in Indexed Operations World — but with §1\n"
"disabled. Now §2 is available, and it transforms the proof.\n"
"\n"
"**Skills required** (all from Worlds 1–4):\n"
"- §3 + §4 for set equality (Subset World)\n"
"- §5 to expose logical structure under complement notation (Set World)\n"
"- §6 and §7 (Indexed Ops World)\n"
"- §8 on hypothesis AND on goal (Set Ops World)\n"
"- Complement reasoning throughout\n"
"\n"
"**Proof strategy**: In each direction, use §9 to expose the\n"
"negation hidden in complement notation. Then §10 to convert indexed\n"
"membership to a quantifier. Then §11 to swap the quantifier\n"
"through the negation."
