#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L18_Boss
msgid "# Boss: Chaining Subsets to Prove Equality\n"
"\n"
"You have two sets §0 and §1 of natural numbers, with three\n"
"hypotheses:\n"
"- §2 — §3 is contained in §4\n"
"- §5 — §6 is contained in the numbers at most 4\n"
"- §7 — every number less than 5 is in §8\n"
"\n"
"Your task: prove §9.\n"
"\n"
"Think about what this means. The hypothesis §10 tells you that\n"
"§11. And from §12 and §13, you can chain:\n"
"§14. Since §15 is the same as §16 for\n"
"natural numbers, this gives §17. Together with\n"
"§18, you get equality by antisymmetry.\n"
"\n"
"This problem integrates the core skills of this world:\n"
"- **§19 or §20** to prove equality\n"
"- **§21** to prove subsets\n"
"- **§22/§23** to unwrap set membership\n"
"- **Chaining subset hypotheses** (transitivity from Level 8)\n"
"- **§24** to bridge arithmetic facts\n"
"\n"
"There are multiple valid strategies. Choose your own path!"
