#: Game.Levels.PreimageWorld.L15_RewriteComposition
msgid "# A New Proof Strategy: Rewriting with Library Theorems\n"
"\n"
"In Levels 6-12, you proved set equalities by §0 —\n"
"reducing to element-wise membership and proving both directions.\n"
"There is another approach: **compose library results via §1**.\n"
"\n"
"Instead of starting from scratch, you can chain the identities you\n"
"already proved as rewrite rules. Each §2 step transforms the\n"
"expression using a known theorem, and after enough rewrites the\n"
"two sides match automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove §3.\n"
"\n"
"You already know:\n"
"- §4: §5\n"
"- §6: §7\n"
"\n"
"Apply them in sequence:\n"
"1. §8 — distribute over §9\n"
"2. §10 — distribute over §11\n"
"\n"
"Two rewrites, no §12, no §13. The library does the work.\n"
"\n"
"This technique scales: the boss level will use the same approach\n"
"with four rewrites to prove that preimage preserves set difference."
msgstr ""

