#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L18_DeMorganUnion
msgid "You proved De Morgan's law for indexed unions:\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"This is the first proof where you used BOTH §1 and\n"
"§2 together. The key insight is how negation swaps\n"
"quantifiers:\n"
"\n"
"| Statement | Negation |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| §3 | §4 |\n"
"| §5 | §6 |\n"
"\n"
"**The logical core**: De Morgan for sets is just De Morgan for\n"
"quantifiers in disguise: §7. The complement §8 is §9, the union §10 is §11,\n"
"and the intersection §12 is §13.\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math: \"§14 means there is no §15\n"
"with §16, which means for every §17, §18, which\n"
"means §19.\"\n"
"\n"
"**Up next**: The dual De Morgan law §20\n"
"— the harder direction, where you will need classical reasoning."
msgstr ""

