#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L07_ImageUnion
msgid "You proved §0. Image distributes over\n"
"union!\n"
"\n"
"The key moves:\n"
"- **Forward**: Destructure image of union, case-split on §1,\n"
"  place the same witness in the correct image\n"
"- **Backward**: Case-split on §2, destructure\n"
"  each image membership, repackage with §3/§4\n"
"\n"
"**The witness transfer pattern again**: Both directions re-use the\n"
"SAME witness §5 -- you destructure to find it, then repackage it\n"
"with updated membership. In the forward direction, §6\n"
"becomes §7 or §8. In the backward direction, §9\n"
"or §10 becomes §11 or §12 for §13.\n"
"\n"
"**§14 on disjunctions**: The backward direction could also be\n"
"done with §15, which\n"
"splits the union of images AND destructures each image membership\n"
"in one step. The §16 in §17 handles §18, just as §19\n"
"handles §20 and §21.\n"
"\n"
"**§22 and §23**: When building anonymous constructors for\n"
"unions, §24 injects into the left side and §25 into\n"
"the right. The alternative is §26 / §27.\n"
"\n"
"**Why this works**: §28 distributes over §29. If §30,\n"
"then §31, and vice versa. The union is §32\n"
"at the predicate level, and image is §33 at the membership level.\n"
"\n"
"**Scoreboard**:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Preimage | Image |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| §34 (union) | ✓ equality | ✓ equality |\n"
"| §35 (intersection) | ✓ equality | ? |\n"
"\n"
"Next: What about intersection?\n"
"\n"
"The library name is §36."
msgstr ""

