#: Game.Levels.PsetImgPreimg.L08_InjectiveIndexedInterImage
msgid "# Indexed Intersection Under Injectivity\n"
"\n"
"In Level 4, you proved §0 —\n"
"only a subset. The reverse direction failed because different indices\n"
"might use different witnesses that cannot be unified into one element\n"
"of the full intersection.\n"
"\n"
"In Level 7, you used the **witness collapse** pattern to close the\n"
"gap for binary intersection. Now do the same for the **indexed** case:\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"The strategy is an indexed version of Level 7's witness collapse.\n"
"For each index §2, you get a witness §3 with\n"
"§4. Injectivity forces all these witnesses to be the same\n"
"element, which therefore belongs to every §5.\n"
"\n"
"**New prerequisite — §6**: This level needs the index type\n"
"§7 to have at least one element, written §8 in the\n"
"function signature. This is a **typeclass**: Lean finds the instance\n"
"automatically. To use it in a proof, write:\n"
"\n"
"§9\n"
"\n"
"The French quotes §10 mean \"retrieve the typeclass instance from\n"
"context.\" After this line, §11 is a concrete index you can use.\n"
"\n"
"Note: §12 (a TYPE has elements) is different from\n"
"§13 (a SET has elements). §14 is about the type\n"
"itself."
msgstr ""

