#: Game.Levels.PsetImgPreimg.L02_ConcreteComputation
msgid "# Computing an Image Concretely\n"
"\n"
"Every other level in this problem set works with ABSTRACT functions\n"
"and sets. This level grounds the theory in a specific computation.\n"
"\n"
"Consider the successor function §0 (which maps §1\n"
"to §2). What is the image of the set of naturals less than 3\n"
"under §3?\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"That is, the set of natural numbers §5 with §6 and §7.\n"
"\n"
"The proof uses the same §8 + §9 pattern as the abstract\n"
"levels, but now the witness arithmetic becomes visible.\n"
"\n"
"**Forward**: given §10, show §11 and §12.\n"
"\n"
"**Backward**: given §13 and §14, the witness is §15.\n"
"\n"
"**Tip**: When a hypothesis or goal involves set membership defined\n"
"by a predicate, that membership is definitionally §16. Use\n"
"§17 to convert a set membership hypothesis into\n"
"its arithmetic form, or §18 to convert a set membership goal.\n"
"This lets §19 see the arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"**Observations** (keep these in mind for later worlds):\n"
"- §20 is **injective**: different inputs always give different\n"
"  outputs.\n"
"- §21 is **NOT surjective**: §22 has no preimage."
msgstr ""

