#: Game.Levels.InjectiveWorld.L03_NonInjective
msgid "You disproved injectivity by finding a counterexample!\n"
"\n"
"**The proof had three parts**:\n"
"1. §0 — assume injectivity\n"
"2. §1 — apply injectivity to a colliding pair\n"
"3. §2 — §3 is absurd, so §4\n"
"\n"
"**Two proof shapes side by side**:\n"
"\n"
"| Proving §5 | Proving §6 |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| §7 | §8 |\n"
"| Show §9 from §10 | Find §11 with §12 |\n"
"| Constructive | By contradiction |\n"
"\n"
"**Why §13 works**: §14 and §15 in ℕ (integer division\n"
"rounds down). So §16 is §17, which is §18.\n"
"\n"
"**Why non-injectivity matters**: A non-injective function **loses\n"
"information** — distinct inputs become indistinguishable after applying\n"
"§19. You cannot recover the original input from the output. In fact,\n"
"§20 has no left inverse (no function §21 with §22 for\n"
"all §23), precisely because the information is lost. You will prove\n"
"the connection between left inverses and injectivity in Level 7.\n"
"\n"
"**Looking ahead**: You have now mastered both directions — proving AND\n"
"disproving injectivity. Next, you will learn how injectivity behaves\n"
"under function composition."
msgstr ""

