#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L20_Boss
msgid "# Boss: f '' (f ⁻¹' t) = t When t ⊆ range f\n"
"\n"
"In Level 14, you proved §0 -- the ⊆ direction\n"
"always holds. Now you will prove the full EQUALITY, under the\n"
"condition that every element of §1 is in the range of §2:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"The hypothesis §4 says: for every §5,\n"
"there exists some §6 with §7. This is exactly the\n"
"surjectivity condition needed to close the gap.\n"
"\n"
"The proof combines several skills from this world:\n"
"- §8 for set equality (Subset World)\n"
"- §9 for biconditional (baseline)\n"
"- Image membership destructuring with §10 (L03)\n"
"- Image membership construction with §11 (L06)\n"
"- Range membership destructuring (L11)\n"
"- Preimage membership unfolding (Preimage World)\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §12 then §13\n"
"2. **⊆ direction**: Destructure image membership, use preimage\n"
"   hypothesis directly (same as Level 14)\n"
"3. **⊇ direction**: From §14, use surjectivity §15 to get\n"
"   §16 with §17, then build image membership"
msgstr ""

