#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L05_NonMembershipExistential
msgid "# Non-Membership with Existential Predicates\n"
"\n"
"In Level 3, you proved §0 — the predicate was a simple\n"
"arithmetic comparison, and §1 dispatched it directly after §2.\n"
"\n"
"But what happens when the predicate involves an **existential**?\n"
"\n"
"The set §3 has predicate §4, which means\n"
"§5. To prove §6, you must show that\n"
"NO witness §7 can satisfy §8.\n"
"\n"
"The proof pattern:\n"
"1. §9 — assume §10, giving §11\n"
"   (i.e., §12)\n"
"2. §13 — destructure the existential: extract the\n"
"   witness §14 and the equation §15\n"
"3. §16 — the equation §17 has no natural number solution\n"
"   (3 is odd), so §18 derives §19\n"
"\n"
"The new tactic here is §20. It takes an existential hypothesis\n"
"and breaks it apart into its components. The syntax uses angle brackets:\n"
"§21 (type ⟨ as §22 and ⟩ as §23).\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that 3 is not even."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L06_SubsetHypAsFunction
msgid "Subset Hypotheses as Functions"
msgstr ""

