msgid "# Nonemptiness Transfers Through Images\n"
"\n"
"If a set §0 is nonempty, then its image §1 is also nonempty.\n"
"This is intuitively obvious: if there is an element in §2, applying\n"
"§3 to it produces an element in §4.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §5 means §6 -- there exists at\n"
"least one element. The proof pattern is different from the subset\n"
"and equality proofs you have been doing: instead of §7/§8,\n"
"you destructure the nonemptiness hypothesis to get a witness, then\n"
"build image membership from that witness.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §9 -- extract the witness from §10\n"
"2. Construct §11 using §12 as the witness"
