#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L01_IndexedUnion
msgid "# Indexed Unions\n"
"\n"
"In Set Operations World, you learned that §0 corresponds to §1:\n"
"an element is in the union if it is in §2 **or** in §3. But what if\n"
"you have not just two sets, but a whole **family** of sets — one for\n"
"each value of some index?\n"
"\n"
"If §4 is a family of sets indexed by §5, the\n"
"**indexed union** §6 collects every element that belongs to\n"
"at least one set in the family:\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"The binary union §8 is the special case with a two-element index\n"
"(§9). The indexed version generalizes §10 to §11:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Notation | Logical meaning |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| Binary union | §12 | §13 |\n"
"| Indexed union | §14 | §15 |\n"
"\n"
"**New tool**: §16 converts §17 into\n"
"§18. After that, you provide the witness index with §19.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: The family §20 for §21\n"
"gives one set for each possible remainder mod 3 (and more).\n"
"Prove that §22 belongs to this indexed union by finding the right\n"
"remainder class."
msgstr ""

