msgid "# The Dual Distributive Law\n"
"\n"
"In the boss (next level), you will prove that indexed union distributes\n"
"over intersection: §0.\n"
"Here, prove the **dual**: indexed intersection distributes over union.\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"This says: being in every §2 OR in §3 is the same as being in\n"
"every §4.\n"
"\n"
"This level integrates §5 with §6 and\n"
"requires case analysis on the union. The **backward direction** needs\n"
"§7 — the classical principle of case analysis — because\n"
"knowing §8 for every §9 does not directly tell you which\n"
"disjunct holds globally.\n"
"\n"
"**About §10**: §11 splits the proof into two\n"
"branches: one where §12 holds, and one where §13 holds.\n"
"This is weaker than §14 (which assumes the negation of the\n"
"whole goal). You used §15 in the De Morgan levels; §16\n"
"is the same classical reasoning applied to a specific proposition."
