"\n"
"In the previous level, you proved that indexed union is monotone:\n"
"if each §0, then §1. Now prove the\n"
"**dual** for indexed intersection:\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"The proof is simpler than the union case because there is no §3\n"
"to extract — both sides are §4 statements. You unwrap the §5 on\n"
"both hypothesis and goal to get universals, then apply the pointwise\n"
"subset.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof strategy**: Unwrap the intersection hypothesis to get\n"
"§6, unwrap the goal to get §7, introduce\n"
"the index, and transfer membership via §8."
msgstr ""

