#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L14_ImagePreimageGap
msgid "# Applying f Then Pulling Back: f '' (f ⁻¹' t) ⊆ t\n"
"\n"
"What happens when you take a preimage and then push it forward?\n"
"\n"
"Starting with a set §0 of outputs, §1 collects all inputs\n"
"that map into §2. Then §3 pushes those inputs\n"
"forward again. Do you get §4 back?\n"
"\n"
"Almost -- but only a SUBSET:\n"
"\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"The ⊆ direction is immediate: if §6, there exists\n"
"§7 with §8. Since §9 means §10,\n"
"and §11, we get §12.\n"
"\n"
"But equality can fail! Elements of §13 that are NOT in the range of\n"
"§14 get \"lost\" -- there is no input that maps to them, so they\n"
"cannot appear in §15.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove the ⊆ direction.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §16 -- destructure image membership\n"
"2. §17 is already the answer!"
msgstr ""

