#. §19: `Set.compl_inter`
#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L13_DeMorgan
msgid "You proved De Morgan's law for sets! The proof combined:\n"
"\n"
"- **§0** — reduce set equality to element-wise biconditional\n"
"- **§1** — convert the negated disjunction (forward direction)\n"
"- **§2** — case analysis on the union hypothesis (backward direction)\n"
"- **Complement application** — §3 applies §4 to §5\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math, this proof reads: \"Let §6. Then\n"
"§7, so §8 and §9 (De Morgan),\n"
"hence §10. Conversely, let §11.\n"
"Suppose §12. If §13, this contradicts §14.\n"
"If §15, this contradicts §16. Either way, contradiction.\"\n"
"\n"
"The library name is §17. In the next level, you will\n"
"prove the dual: §18 (§19)."
msgstr ""

