#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L18_DeMorganUnion
msgid "# De Morgan's Law for Indexed Unions\n"
"\n"
"In Set Operations World, you proved De Morgan's law for binary unions:\n"
"§0. Now prove the indexed generalization:\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"In words: an element is outside the union of a family if and only if\n"
"it is outside every member of the family. This is the set-theoretic\n"
"version of the logical equivalence §2.\n"
"\n"
"This is the first level that requires BOTH §3 and\n"
"§4 in the same proof — one for each side of the equation.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**: Use §5 and §6 as usual. In each\n"
"direction, the complement turns §7 into §8 (an implication to\n"
"§9), and you bridge between §10 and §11 through the\n"
"negation of quantifiers."
msgstr ""

