#: Game.Levels.PsetImgPreimg.L07_InjectiveInterImage
msgid "You proved that injectivity closes the intersection gap!\n"
"\n"
"The proof had four key steps:\n"
"1. §0 — destructure both\n"
"   image memberships\n"
"2. §1 — apply injectivity to get §2\n"
"3. §3 — rewrite to get §4\n"
"4. §5 — build the image of the intersection\n"
"\n"
"**The witness collapse pattern**: Steps 2 and 3 are the defining proof\n"
"move for injectivity in image/preimage proofs. You have two witnesses\n"
"(§6 and §7) that map to the same output. Injectivity collapses them\n"
"into one (§8), letting you combine their set memberships. Watch\n"
"for this pattern — you will use it in every remaining level.\n"
"\n"
"**Why does injectivity help?** If §9, there\n"
"exist §10 and §11 with §12. Without\n"
"injectivity, §13 and §14 might differ, so neither is in §15.\n"
"With injectivity, §16 forces §17, so the single element\n"
"belongs to both §18 and §19.\n"
"\n"
"**Combined with §20 from Image World**, you now have:\n"
"\n"
"§21\n"
"\n"
"The \\\\subseteq direction (Image World L08) was unconditional; the\n"
"\\\\supseteq direction (this level) required injectivity.\n"
"\n"
"**The full biconditional**: This result is not just a sufficient\n"
"condition — injectivity is NECESSARY. If §22\n"
"for ALL §23, then §24 must be injective. To see why: suppose\n"
"§25. Take §26 and §27. Then\n"
"§28 is nonempty, so by the equality\n"
"hypothesis §29 is nonempty, which forces\n"
"§30 to be nonempty, so §31. In other words,\n"
"\"image preserves all binary intersections\" is a *characterization*\n"
"of injectivity, not just a consequence.\n"
"\n"
"**Looking ahead**: You will study §32 extensively\n"
"in Injective World, where you will prove injectivity for specific\n"
"functions, compose injections, and extract injectivity from\n"
"compositions."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.PreimageWorld.L03_PreimageNonInjective
msgid "Both 0 and 1000 are in the preimage because the function always outputs 7, and 7 < 10."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `¬(s ⊆ t)`
#. §1: `¬ P`
#. §2: `P → False`
#. §3: `¬(s ⊆ t)`
#. §4: `intro h`
#. §5: `h : s ⊆ t`
#. §6: `False`
#. §7: `s`
#. §8: `t`
#. §9: `False`
#. §10: `{n | n < 5} ⊆ {n | n < 3}`
#. §11: `intro h`
#. §12: `False`
#. §13: `4 ∈ {n | n < 5}`
#. §14: `h`
#. §15: `4 ∈ {n | n < 3}`
#. §16: `4 < 3`
#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L07_NonSubset
msgid "# When ⊆ Fails: Proving ¬(s ⊆ t)\n"
"\n"
"All the subset proofs so far have been **positive**: you showed that\n"
"one set is contained in another. But what if the containment is\n"
"**false**? How do you prove §0?\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §1 is defined as §2. So to prove §3,\n"
"you use §4 to **assume** the subset holds, getting\n"
"§5, and then derive a contradiction (§6).\n"
"\n"
"To derive the contradiction, exhibit a **counterexample**: find an\n"
"element that is in §7 but not in §8. If the subset held, this\n"
"element would have to be in both — but it is not, so we get §9.\n"
"\n"
"In Level 1, we noted that §10 is false\n"
"because 4 is in the first set but not the second. Now you will prove\n"
"this formally.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §11 — assume the subset holds (goal becomes §12)\n"
"2. Prove §13 — show the witness is in the domain\n"
"3. Apply §14 to get §15 — use the assumed subset\n"
"4. Unwrap and derive contradiction — §16 is false"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f a = f b`
#. §1: `ha : r (g (f b)) = f a`
#. §2: `hb : r (g (f b)) = f b`
#. §3: `rw [← ha, hb]`
#: Game.Levels.InjectiveWorld.L08_Boss
msgid "The goal is §0. You have §1 and\n"
"§2. Chain them: §3."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `hy : f x ∈ t`
#. §1: `y ∈ t`
#. §2: `y = f x`
#. §3: `f x ∈ f '' (f ⁻¹' t)`
#. §4: `x`
#. §5: `x ∈ f ⁻¹' t`
#. §6: `f x ∈ t`
#. §7: `hy`
#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L20_Boss
msgid "After substitution, §0 (was §1, now\n"
"§2). The goal is §3.\n"
"\n"
"Build the image membership: the witness is §4, and §5\n"
"is §6 which is §7."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L13_SetNonEquality
msgid "The set of numbers less than 3 is not equal to the set of\n"
"numbers less than 5."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L06_ImageMonotonicity
msgid "If s ⊆ t then f '' s ⊆ f '' t."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `congrArg f h`
#. §1: `f a = f b`
#. §2: `h : a = b`
#. §3: ```
#. exact congrArg f h    -- from h : a = b, get f a = f b
#. ```
#. §4: `h : a = b`
#. §5: `f`
#. §6: `f`
#. §7: ```
#. -- hab : f a = f b, g : β → γ
#. exact congrArg g hab    -- produces g (f a) = g (f b)
#. ```
#: Game.Metadata
msgid "§0 produces §1 from §2. It says\n"
"\\\\\"applying the same function to equal inputs gives equal outputs.\\\\\"\n"
"\n"
"## Syntax\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"## When to use it\n"
"When you have an equation §4 and want to apply a function §5\n"
"to both sides. This is the Lean formalization of the mathematical step\n"
"\\\\\"apply §6 to both sides of the equation.\\\\\"\n"
"\n"
"## Example\n"
"§7"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `intro x hx`
#. §1: `exact ⟨x, hx, rfl⟩`
#. §2: `f ⁻¹' (f '' s) ⊆ s`
#. §3: `f x ∈ f '' s`
#. §4: `x ∈ s`
#. §5: `f x ∈ f '' s`
#. §6: `x' ∈ s`
#. §7: `f x' = f x`
#. §8: `f`
#. §9: `x'`
#. §10: `x`
#. §11: `x`
#. §12: `s`
#. §13: `f`
#. §14: `f x' = f x`
#. §15: `x' = x`
#. §16: `x' ∈ s`
#. §17: `x ∈ s`
#. §18: `f '' (f ⁻¹' t) ⊆ t`
#. §19: `t`
#. §20: `s ⊆ f ⁻¹' (f '' s)`
#. §21: `f`
#. §22: `f`
#. §23: `Set.subset_preimage_image`
#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L15_PreimageImageGap
msgid "The proof was just §0 then §1.\n"
"Constructing image membership with the same element you started with.\n"
"\n"
"**Why equality fails**: The reverse §2 would\n"
"require: if §3, then §4. But §5 only\n"
"means there exists SOME §6 with §7. If §8 is not\n"
"injective, §9 might differ from §10, and §11 might not be in §12.\n"
"\n"
"**When does equality hold?** If §13 is INJECTIVE: §14\n"
"implies §15, so §16 gives §17. You will prove this\n"
"in the problem set.\n"
"\n"
"**Summary of the two gaps**:\n"
"\n"
"| Statement | Holds? | Equality requires |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| §18 | Always | Surjectivity onto §19 |\n"
"| §20 | Always | Injectivity of §21 |\n"
"\n"
"The image-preimage gap and the preimage-image gap are controlled by\n"
"different properties of §22. This asymmetry is one of the central\n"
"insights of this course.\n"
"\n"
"The library name is §23."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [Set.preimage_inter]`
